                    <h3>Big Data for Healthcare</h3>
                    <iframe width="350" height="300" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/wOwept5WlWM" frameborder="0"
                            allowfullscreen></iframe>
                    <p>Big data has enabled huge savings with about more than 300 billion in a year. Expenditure in
                        clinical is the maximum with about 108 billion. This is in waste if the figure goes increasing
                        each year. According to Loudhouse, commissioned by SAP, many businesses in United States and
                        United Kingdom are investing in big data analytics. It has been found that 78% of the businesses
                        in United States will be making it as a priority in 5 years and thus 88% of the business agree
                        that big data analytics minimizes risk. 94% of organizations in US that have been using big data
                        analytics in healthcare environment, has showed positive impact on their businesses. "A big data
                        revolution is on the way in health care environment starting with the vastly increased supply of
                        information. Recent technical advances have also made it quite easier to collect and analyze the
                        data and information from across multiple sources."</p>
                    <p>Johns Hopkins researchers are spending $600,000 grant to build a databank on cloud from the
                        pediatric MRI medical image data which helps predict abnormalities in patient. The large amount
                        of medical image data from this databank can be used by the doctors to compare image that help
                        identify abnormalities in the patients records over a period of time and identify new
                        discoveries at the exact location in the brain. They are creating data bank of pediatric brain
                        MRI that will allow doctor to diagnose disorders like psychiatric or epilepsy based on previous
                        brain MRI of children's with similar disorders. Medical MRI image data helps doctor make a
                        detail study of brain structure and record latest change in structure that is causing the
                        disorder. This databank acts as search engines in medical industry like Yahoo or Google. These
                        images contain all diagnostic details of psychiatric, epilepsy or infections. Image contains
                        details of 250 regions of the brain's structural measurement.</p>
